
[1]upbraiding

   UPBRA'IDING, ppr. Accusing; casting in the teeth; reproaching;
   reproving.

   UPBRA'IDING, n.

   1. A charging with something wrong or disgraceful; the act of
   reproaching or reproving.

   I have too long borne your blunt upbraidings.

   2. The reproaches or accusations of conscience.
